 is more active than} 8... Qd8 {, where the queen would later get in the way of the rooks.}) 9. O-O Be7 {Black follows a simple development pattern. After short castling, the light-squared bishop should be fianchettoed with ... b6 and ... Bb7 .} 10. Bg5 O-O 11. Qd2 b6 {The usual setup. The bishop is best on b7 .} 12. Rfd1 Bb7 13. Rac1 Rac8 {The next move can be ... Rfd8 . Both sides have mobilized their forces and a complicated middle game lies ahead. Black's play is directed against the d4 -pawn, which is a long term weakness.} *

