 good idea:} fxe5 20. Qxe5 Nf4 {White has big problems. There is a threat of} 21. Z0 Bc6 {with an attack against the g2 -pawn or Nxe2+ Qxe2} 22. Bb5 {, winning an exchange.}) 19... Bc6 ({Now} 19... fxe5 20. Qxe5 Nf4 {is a threat, taking aim at the g2 -pawn. In addition, Black plans to drive away the knight from d6 with ...Rad8 (with the threat of ...fxe5 ). The position is equal.}) 20. f4 {White tries to fortify the e5 -pawn. But this runs into surprising problems.} fxe5 21. fxe5 ({No better is} 21. Qxe5 Rad8 22. Ne4 Rf5 23. Qd4 Rd7 $1 {∓ The rook goes to a protected square, after which White can no longer defend the f4 -pawn.}) 21... Qg5 {Now knight moves are threatening to attack g2 .} 22. g3 Ne3 23. Rxf8+ Rxf8 {White's king position is permanently weakened. Black has a big advantage. The white queen is tied to protecting the e5 -pawn, making defense difficult.} *

