is better to just sacrifice the pawn, because the exchange of the black knight for the bishop and the resulting change in the pawn structure are favorable for Black.} Nxf4 10. gxf4 {The pawn on f4 is weak in the long term, and there is no dark-squared bishop to defend it.} dxc3 {Otherwise White could capture on d4 and play against the weak pawn on d4 .} 11. Nxc3 Be7 {The pawns f4 and d3 are weak, while there are no weak pawns in the black camp. The moves ... O-O , ... Bd7 and ... Rfd8 are now on the agenda. The d3 -pawn can then be targeted with ... Be8 . Black has the better chances.} *

