treat to. Although Black has only developed one piece so far and has not yet brought their king to safety, the aggressive flank play is justified and dangerous for White.} ({The center is closed and the black king has nothing to fear for the time being. The game now becomes very sharp. The more solid alternative is} 7... Ne7 {. White can now try to weaken Black's control of d4 with} 8. b4 $5 {. After} cxb4 {(or 8...Ng6 )} 9. Nxd4 {a complicated position arises with chances for both sides.}) 8. h3 {A natural reaction and the most common choice in tournament practice. Nevertheless, the move is a mistake: it gives Black the pawn break ... g5 - g4 , which leads to a dangerous opening on the kingside.} h5 9. Nh2 {White takes control of the g4 -square and hopes to prevent ... g5 - g4 .} g4 {White's hopes were unfounded! Of course the g-pawn can be sacrificed to open files.} 10. hxg4 ({We looked at} 10. Na3 gxh3 {via the move order Na3} 11. g4 {Nh2 gxh3 .}) 10... Nh6 ({A novelty. Black prepares to capture on g4 . The obvious} 10... hxg4 {also leads to an advantage for Black, but after} 11. Qxg4 {the queen can then help with the defense, e.g.} dxc3 12. Be4 {, Quillan-Koneru 2012 .}) 11. Be4 {Through the opposition of the bishops, White wants to weaken Black's kingside attack and prepare development of the queenside with d2 - d3 .} Nxg4 {The knight on h2 is passive, but it defends the white king and is therefore exchanged. Black is threatening ... Qh4 .} 12. Nxg4 ({Or} 12. Nf3 d3 $1 {, after which it is difficult to suggest moves for White. Black can play ...a7-a6 , ...b7-b5 and ...c5-c4 to further constrict the white queenside.}) 12... hxg4 13. Qxg4 ({Forced. Black was threatening ...Qh4 and} 13. g3 Qg5 {doesn't help.}) 13... Rh4 14. Qf3 d3 {The final nail in the coffin for the white queenside! White is prevented from developing naturally with d2 - d3 . Developing the queenside is now a mammoth task. Meanwhile, Black is threatening to win the e-pawn with ... Bg7 or ... Qg5 , and a mating attack on the h-file is also possible at any time.} ({Black is clearly better. Qxd3 loses a piece after} 14... Rxe4 {.}) *

