osition.}) 5. Bg2 Bb7 {From here the bishop puts pressure on the e4 -pawn, which can be further attacked with ... Nf6 and ... b5 - b4 .} 6. O-O Nf6 {Black is threatening to win the e-pawn with ...b5-b4 . White could defend against this or sacrifice the pawn for initiative with d4 .} 7. d3 {After that, the game remains in the territory of the Closed Sicilian. To me this seems to be far less dangerous than an early d2 - d4 .} ({We consider} 7. d4 cxd4 8. Nxd4 {via the move order d4 cxd4 Nxd4 Nf6 O-O .}) 7... d6 ({Here as well, Black should take control of the e5 -square.} 7... Be7 $2 {allows the typical tactic} 8. e5 Bxg2 9. exf6 Bxf1 10. fxe7 Qxe7 11. Qxf1 {.}) 8. h3 {White wants push their kingside pawns: g3 - g4 , f2 - f4 and Ng3 would be a typical setup.} Nc6 {I like this better than developing the knight to d7 , as the knight has more influence on the center here. Black can become later active in the center with ... d6 - d5 . In addition, Black keeps the d7 -square free, which can be useful in case of g3 - g4 - g5 .} 9. Be3 {A natural developing move and White's most frequent choice.} Be7 10. f4 ({White continues the play on the kingside. It is too late for a transition to an Open Sicilian:} 10. d4 $2 cxd4 11. Nxd4 Ne5 {White has lost too much time here. Black is threatening to win a pawn with ...b5-b4 and the knight could soon move to c4 .}) 10... O-O {The white attack is very slow, so the black king has little to fear on the kingside. Black has a good position. On the agenda is play in the center with ... d6 - d5 or on the queenside with ... b5 - b4 and ... a6 - a5 -a4 .} ({After g4} 10... d5 {the black play in the center is stronger than the white attack on the kingside, e.g.:   A ) g5} 11. d4 {gxf6 Bxf6⩱ .}) ({B ) After} 10... e5 {Nd7} 11. Bf2 {Black could play} g5 $5 {to win a pawn. The less sharp f6 exf6 Nxf6⩱ is also good.}) ({C ) Bf2 dxe4 dxe4} 10... Qc7 {with some advantage for Black, who will bring a rook to d8 next. Then ...Nd4 is possible. If White attacks the knight f6 , it will be transferred to the queenside via d7 .}) *

