win the queen.} Be7 17. Bd4 ({After} 17. Bc5 $2 Bxc5 18. Rxe6+ fxe6 {Black has too much material for the queen.}) 17... Qg4 18. Bc5 {White wins back the piece.} O-O ({After} 18... Nc6 19. Bxe7 Nxe7 20. Qxa3 {Black must also part with the extra piece, because} Qg5 21. Re4 Kf8 $2 22. Rd1 {is not a good idea.}) 19. Bxe7 Re8 20. Bxa3 Nc6 {The material balance is restored. White must now be a little careful, because the light squares around the king are weakened and the black knight is on its way over there.} *

