in, a possible transposition to the Open Sicilian is on the horizon. Those who play the Taimanov Sicilian have no reason to avoid this. I then recommend . Reaching a Four Knights Sicilian, however, is no longer possible, so I suggest to transpose into an isolated pawn structure with d5 here. The passive} 5. d3 {presents no challenges for Black. After} d5 {Black is at least equal. The white bishop on e2 is poorly placed.}) 5... d6 {Black allows the Open Sicilian.} 6. d4 ({Harmless is} 6. d3 {because with the passive bishop on e2 , it is unclear what plan White is pursuing. Black plays} Be7 {followed by ...O-O . The queenside can be developed with ...a7-a6 , ...b7-b5 , and ...Bb7 .}) 6... cxd4 7. Nxd4 Be7 {We have reached the Scheveningen Variation. It is a flexible version for Black, as the moves ... a7 - a6 and ... Qc7 have not yet been played.} *

